Two separate issues:

**1. `StaticResource` vs `DynamicResource`**

`StaticResource` resolves **once** at load time. To react to runtime dictionary swaps, use `DynamicResource`:

```xml
<!-- ❌ Won't update at runtime -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✅ Updates when the merged dictionary changes -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap themes by replacing the merged dictionary:

```csharp
var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDicts.Clear();
mergedDicts.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

**2. Activity restart on config change**

By default, Android destroys and recreates the Activity when `uiMode` changes. Add this attribute to your `MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.UiMode | ConfigChanges.Orientation | ConfigChanges.ScreenSize)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

This tells Android to notify instead of restart. Then override to apply the new theme:

```csharp
public override void OnConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig)
{
    base.OnConfigurationChanged(newConfig);

    bool isDark = (newConfig.UiMode & UiMode.NightMask) == UiMode.NightYes;
    // swap your ResourceDictionary here
}
```

**TL;DR:** `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` fixes runtime switching; `ConfigChanges.UiMode` fixes the restart.
